lead_paragraph: Hillary Clinton brought a close to the presidential primary season with a win Tuesday in the nation's capital and a meeting with dispatched rival Bernie Sanders, hoping to set a tone of Democratic unity heading into next month's party convention in Philadelphia.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Wins DC Primary, as She Meets With Sanders
